nter;\" | <ref>{{cite news|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/02/20/nickelodeon-announces-nominations-for-the-28th-annual-kids-choice-awards/365877/|title=Nickelodeon Announces Nominations for the '28th Annual Kids\u2019 Choice Awards'|date=February 20, 2015|publisher=[[Zap2it]]|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/02/20/kids-choice-awards-release-nominations-meryl-streep-earns-her-very-first|title=Meryl Streep gets her first Kids' Choice Awards nomination: See the full list|date=February 20, 2015|publisher=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=February 21, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[2017 Kids' Choice Awards|Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite TV Show \u2013 Kids' Show\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nickpress.com/press-releases/2017/02/02/nickelodeon-announces-2017-kids-choice-awards-nominations|title=NICKELODEON ANNOUNCES 2017 KIDS\u2019 CHOICE AWARDS NOMINATIONS {{!}} Nick Press|website=NickPress|access-date=2017-03-08}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|3596176}}\n\n{{Former Nickelodeon original series}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American comedy television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2018 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:Nickelodeon shows]]\n[[Category:Television series about families]]\n[[Category:Television series about siblings]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American sitcom}}\n{{Infobox television \n| image                = Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn logo.gif\n| genre                = [[Comedy]]\n| creator              = [[Matt Fleckenstein]]\n| developer            = [[Michael Feldman (writer)|Michael Feldman]]\n| starring             = {{plainlist |\n* [[Brian Stepanek]]\n* [[Allison Munn]]\n* [[Aidan Gallagher]]\n* Casey Simpson\n* Mace Coronel\n* [[Lizzy Greene]]\n* Gabrielle Elyse\n* Kyla-Drew Simmons\n}}\n| theme_music_composer = [[Doug Rockwell]]\n| composer             = {{plainlist |\n* Chris Lee\n* Scott Clausen\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 4\n| num_episodes         = 82\n| list_episodes        = List of Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn episodes\n| executive_producer   = {{plainlist |\n* Michael Feldman\n* Matt Fleckenstein\n* Douglas Danger Lieblein\n* David DiPietro\n* Paul Ciancarelli\n}}\n| producer             = {{plainlist |\n* Barbara Brace\n* Andrew Hill Newman\n* [[Sarah Jane Cunningham]] & [[Suzie V. Freeman]]\n}}\n| cinematography       = {{plainlist |\n* Patti Lee\n* John W. Simmons\n}}\n| camera               = [[Multi-camera]]\n| runtime              = 22\u201323 minutes\n| company              = {{plainlist |\n* [[Nickelodeon Productions]]\n}}\n| network              = [[Nickelodeon]]\n| picture_format       = [[HDTV]] [[720p]]\n| audio_format         = [[5.1 surround sound]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2014|9|13}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|2018|8|4}}\n| website              = https://www.nick.com/shows/nicky-ricky-dicky-and-dawn\n}}\n\n'''''Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn''''' is an American [[comedy]] television series developed by [[Michael Feldman (writer)|Michael Feldman]] and created by [[Matt Fleckenstein]] that aired on [[Nickelodeon]] from September 13, 2014 to August 4, 2018. The series stars [[Brian Stepanek]], [[Allison Munn]], [[Aidan Gallagher]], Casey Simpson, Mace Coronel, [[Lizzy Greene]], Gabrielle Elyse, and Kyla-Drew Simmons.\n\n== Premise ==\nThe series focuses on [[quadruplets]] Nicky, Ricky, Dicky, and Dawn Harper, nine years old at the start of the series,<ref>{{cite episode|series=Nicky, Ricky, Dicky, and Dawn|title=Mall in the Family|author=Ricky Harper|minutes=2:00|quote=She's eleven.}}</ref> who have nothing in common and often fight, but must work together to solve everyday situations.\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{main|List of Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn episodes}}\n{{:List of Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn episodes}}\n\n== Cast and characters ==\n\n=== Main ===\n* [[Brian Stepanek]] as Tom, the father of the Harper family quadruplets. It is a running gag in the series that he cares more about his possessions than his children, but he loves his family and is a kid at heart.\n* [[Allison Munn]] as Anne, the mother of the Harper family quadruplets who usually gets caught up in Tom's new obsessions.\n* [[Aidan Gallagher]] as Nicky, the youngest of the Harper quadruplets. He is shown to be quite comedic, quirky, and easily confused.\n* Casey Simpson as Ricky, is the second oldest of the Harper quadruplets. He is the smart one of the group, always seen carrying a book or doing his homework. He is also a neat freak and a bit of a goody two-shoes, though he occasionally tries to prove to Dawn and his brothers that he can bend rules as well.\n* Mace Coronel as Dicky, the third oldest and easy-going Harper quadruplet who cares a great deal about his appearance. He always takes the easy way out. He ships himself to Australia in \"[[List of Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn episodes#ep78|Quadcodile Dundee]]\".\n* [[Lizzy Greene]] as Dawn, the oldest of the Harper quadruplets. Although she's always seen bothering her brothers, she does care about them deeply. There is a consistent rivalry for the leader spot of the quads between her and Ricky.\n* Gabrielle Elyse as Josie (season 1), a worker at Tom's sporting shop and babysitter for Nicky, Ricky, Dicky and Dawn.<!-- Note: Gabrielle Elyse is main cast credited, but only for the episodes she appears in. -->\n* Kyla-Drew Simmons as Mae (recurring, seasons 1\u20132; main, seasons 3\u20134), the quads' friend and Dawn's best friend. She often calls herself \"the fifth quad\".\n\n=== Recurring ===\n* Lincoln Melcher as Mack (seasons 1\u20133)\n* Jason Sims-Prewitt as Principal Tarian (seasons 2\u20133)\n* [[Siena Agudong]] as Natlee (seasons 2\u20134)\n* Hayden Crawford as Dooley (seasons 3\u20134)\n* Theodore John Barnes as Miles (seasons 3\u20134)\n* Isabella Revel as Avery (seasons 3\u20134)\n* Ariana Molkara as Sadie (season 4)\n\n== Production ==\nThe series was originally picked up for 13 episodes on March 13, 2014, but was later increased to 20 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/03/nickelodeon-greenlights-new-comedy-from-dan-schneider-two-other-live-action-series-698354/|title=Nickelodeon Greenlights New Comedy from Dan Schneider, Two Other Live-Action Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|date=March 13, 2014|access-date=August 4, 2014}}</ref> The series premiered on September 13, 2014. On November 18, 2014, the series was renewed for a second season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/11/18/henry-danger-and-nicky-ricky-dicky-dawn-renewed-for-second-seasons-by-nickelodeon/329224/|title=Henry Danger and Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn Renewed for Second Seasons by Nickelodeon|work=TV by the Numbers|date=November 18, 2014|access-date=November 18, 2014}}</ref> The second season premiered on May 23, 2015. On February 9, 2016, Nickelodeon renewed ''Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn'' for a third season of 14 episodes. It was also confirmed that Matt Fleckenstein would step down as show runner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/nicky-ricky-dicky-dawn-renewed-third-season-nickelodeon-1201699342/|title=Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn Renewed for Season Three by Nickelodeon; Creator Exits|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=February 9, 2016|access-date=February 11, 2016}}</ref> Actress Lizzy Greene announced on her [[Twitter]] account that production for season three started on April 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/greene_lizzy/status/724993450139996160|title=Season 3 starts today can't wait for you guys to see|work=Twitter|author=Lizzy Greene|date=April 26, 2016|access-date=May 11, 2016}}</ref> The third season premiered on January 7, 2017. The series was renewed for a fourth season and had its episode order for the third season increased from 14 to 24 by Nickelodeon on March 20, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/03/nicky-ricky-dicky-dawn-renewed-season-4-nickelodeon-1202045866/|title=Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn Renewed for Season 4 by Nickelodeon|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=March 20, 2017|access-date=March 20, 2017}}</ref> On October 4, 2017, it was announced that Mace Coronel would be leaving both ''Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn'', about five episodes before the end of the fourth season, and Nickelodeon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/10/nicky-ricky-dicky-dawn-mace-coronel-abruptly-exits-nickelodeon-comedy-series-1202182216/|title=Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn Future in Limbo After Star Mace Coronel Abruptly Exits Hit Nickelodeon Series|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=October 4, 2017|access-date=October 4, 2017}}</ref> On November 15, 2017, Nickelodeon announced that the fourth season would be the last.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/11/nicky-ricky-dicky-dawn-school-of-rock-canceled-nickelodeon-1202209138/|title=Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn and School of Rock Canceled by Nickelodeon|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Nellie Andreeva|date=November 15, 2017|access-date=November 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Ratings ===\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_timeslot     = y\n| hide_tv_season    = y\n| hide_rank         = y\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = List of Nicky, Ricky, Dicky & Dawn episodes#Season 1 (2014\u201315)\n| episodes1         = 20<!-- should reflect the number of episodes that contribute to the average given in the last column -->\n| start1            = {{Start date|2014|9|13}}\n| end1              = {{End date|2015|3|24}}\n| startrating1      = 1.60<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-saturday-cable-originals-9-13-2014.html|title=Top 25 Saturday Cab