" width=44%|Defenses\n|-\n!1\n|align=left |{{flagicon|Philippines}} Stephen Loman<br/><small>def. Gary Mangat</small>\n|align=center | Brave CF 9: The Kingdom of Champions <br><small>Isa Town, Bahrain</small>\n|align=center | November 17, 2017\n|\n<small>'''1.''' def. Frans Mlambo at Brave CF 13: European Evolution on June 9, 2018<br />'''2.''' def. Felipe Efrain at Brave CF 18 on November 16, 2018<br />'''3.''' def. Elias Boudegzdame at Brave CF 22: Storm of Warriors on March 15, 2019<br />'''4.''' def. Louie Sanoudakis at Brave CF 30 on November 23, 2019</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Events==\nBrave Combat Federation has held events in 19 countries during its three-plus years of operations. Brave has been to [[Bahrain]], [[Brazil]], the [[United Arab Emirates]], [[India]], [[Kazakhstan]], [[Mexico]], [[Jordan]], [[Indonesia]], [[Northern Ireland]], [[Morocco]], [[Colombia]], [[Pakistan]], [[South Africa]], [[Saudi Arabia]], the [[Philippines]], [[England]], [[Romania]], [[Kyrgyzstan]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmaindia.com/brave-cf-to-make-kyrgyzstan-debut-with-hayder-hassan-debuting-against-carl-booth/|title=BRAVE CF to make Kyrgyzstan debut with Hayder Hassan debuting against Carl Booth - MMA India|publisher=}}</ref>, [[Slovenia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lowkickmma.com/brave-announce-first-show-of-2020-to-be-held-in-solvenia/|title=BRAVE CF Announce First Show Of 2020 To Be Held In Slovenia - Low Kick MMA|publisher=}}</ref>, and will make its Sweden debut soon.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kimura.se/brave-fc-arrangerar-gala-i-sverige-tillsammans-med-akfc/|title=Brave CF arrangerar gala i Sverige tillsammans med AKFC - Kimura.se|publisher=}}</ref> Due to the [[Coronavirus]] pandemic, the promotion has announced that the upcoming three shows will be postponed until a later date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mmaweekly.com/brave-cf-postpones-all-events-until-further-notice|title=BRAVE CF POSTPONES ALL EVENTS UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE - MMA Weekly|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe expansion of Brave has been a wish of president [[Mohammed \"The Hawk\" Shahid]], who claimed the idea behind going to different continents is to provide athletes with a truly global platform so they can showcase their talents, give opportunities to local fighters to shine in the international stage,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fightersonlymag.com/features/royal-rumble-prince-turning-bahrain-global-mma-force/|title=Royal Rumble: How a prince is turning Bahrain into a global MMA force - Fighters Only|publisher=}}</ref> as well as show that Brave is \"the fastest-growing promotion in the world\" <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bravefights.com/brave-confirms-eight-worldwide-events-for-rest-of-2018/|title=BRAVE CONFIRMS EIGHT WORLDWIDE EVENTS FOR REST OF 2018 - BRAVE Fights|publisher=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size:85%; text-align:left; width:80%;\"\n|-\n!Upcoming Events\n!Country\n!Location\n!Date\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 37: Al-Selawe vs Chimaev\n|{{Flag icon|Sweden}} [[Sweden]]\n|Solnahallen, [[Stockholm]]\n|Postponed\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 36: Brewin vs Patterson\n|{{Flag icon|Romania}} [[Romania]]\n|BT Arena, [[Cluj Napoca]]\n|Postponed\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 35: Predator vs Kutateladze\n|{{Flag icon|Brazil}} [[Brazil]]\n|[[Balne\u00e1rio Cambori\u00fa]]\n|Postponed\n|-\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" style=\"font-size:85%; text-align:left; width:80%;\"\n|-\n!Past Events\n!Country\n!Location\n!Date\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 34\n|{{Flag icon|Slovenia}} [[Slovenia]]\n|Halal Tivoli, [[Ljubljana]]\n|January 19, 2020\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 33: Aliskerov vs Gonzalez\n|{{Flag icon|Saudi Arabia}} [[Saudi Arabia]]\n|Prince Abdullah Al Faisal Stadium, [[Jeddah]]\n|December 27, 2019\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 32: Booth vs Hassan\n|{{Flag icon|Kyrgyzstan}} [[Kyrgyzstan]]\n|Sport Palace Kozhomkul, [[Bishkek]]\n|December 14, 2019\n|-\n|-\n|BRAVE CF 31: Hanekom vs Gaucho\n|{{Flag icon|South Africa}} [[South Africa]]\n|Sibaya Casino, [[Durban]]\n|December 7, 2019\n|-