\n  |percentage = 0.71\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = California Republican Party\n  |candidate  = Robert Newman ([[Write-in candidate|write-in]])\n  |votes      = 219\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Independent politician\n  |candidate  = James Harris (write-in)\n  |votes      = 46\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Independent politician\n  |candidate  = Donald Etkes (write-in)\n  |votes      = 43\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Independent politician\n  |candidate  = [[Elisha Shapiro]] (write-in)\n  |votes      = 43\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Independent politician\n  |candidate  = Vibert Greene (write-in)\n  |votes      = 18\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Independent politician\n  |candidate  = Dealphria Tarver (write-in)\n  |votes      = 6\n  |percentage = 0.00\n}}\n{{Election box invalid no change|\n  |votes      = 219,643\n  |percentage = 2.47\n}}\n{{Election box total no change|\n  |votes      = 8,679,423\n  |percentage = 100.00\n}}\n{{Election box turnout no change|\n  |percentage = 32.77\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link without swing|\n  |winner     = California Republican Party\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n'''Results by county'''\n\nResults showed Schwarzenegger won 52 counties while Angelides won 6 (Schwarzenegger won an absolute majority in 48 counties and a plurality in 4 counties while Angelides won an absolute majority in 2 counties and a plurality in 4 counties).  Schwarzenegger won large majorities in California's rural counties, the populous [[Southern California]] counties of [[San Diego County, California|San Diego]], [[Orange County, California|Orange]], [[Riverside County, California|Riverside]], [[San Bernardino County, California|San Bernardino]], and [[Ventura County, California|Ventura]], as well as populous [[Sacramento County, California|Sacramento]], [[Fresno County, California|Fresno]], and [[Kern County, California|Kern]] counties in the [[Central Valley (California)|Central Valley]]. The results were closely contested in [[Los Angeles County, California|Los Angeles County]] and in [[San Francisco Bay Area|Bay Area]] [[suburb]]an counties. Angelides won substantially only in [[Alameda County, California|Alameda]] and [[San Francisco]] counties.<ref name=\"results\"/>\n\n{| style=\"width:75%;\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:lightgrey;\"\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| County\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| [[Arnold Schwarzenegger|Schwarzenegger]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Votes\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| [[Phil Angelides|Angelides]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Votes\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| [[Peter Camejo|Camejo]]\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Votes\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Others\n! style=\"width:7%;\"| Votes\n|-\n|align=\"center\" {{party shading/Republican}}|[[Glenn County, California|Glenn]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''76.50%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''5,775''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''18.82%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''1,421''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1.46%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''110''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''3.22%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''243''\n|-\n|align=\"center\" {{party shading/Republican}}|[[Modoc County, California|Modoc]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''75.20%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''2,829''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''19.22%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''723''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1.25%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''47''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''4.33%'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|''163''\n|-\n|align=\"center\" {{party shading/Republican}}|[[Tehama County, California|Tehama]]\n| 